description:
Queen's Catastrophe



Aired on 01/06/2014, Narrated by: Jonathan Aris



On 12 November 2001, just two months after the September 11 attacks, American Airlines Flight 587, an Airbus A300B4-605R, spirals out of control after taking off from John F. Kennedy Airport. Shortly after, the aircraft crashes into the suburb of Queens, killing all 260 people on board, as well as five on the ground.
